Sentencas: This paper presents a performance analysis of a planar solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with different support structures, i.e., electrode (anode and cathode) and electrolyte supports.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures

Sentencas: An electrochemical model, taking into account structural and operational parameters and gas diffusion at the electrodes, is used to analyze the characteristics of the planar SOFC.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures

Sentencas: Simulation results demonstrate that under cell operation at an intermediate temperature (1073 K), an anode-supported SOFC is superior to an electrolyte- and cathode-supported SOFC.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures

Sentencas: Analysis of individual cell voltage loss indicates that ohmic loss dominates the performance of an electrolyte-supported SOFC whereas activation and ohmic overpotentials constitute the major loss in an electrode-supported counterpart.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures

Sentencas: Sensitivity analyses of the anode-supported SOFC show that decreasing the electrolyte and anode thickness can improve cell performance.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures

Sentencas: A decrease in operating temperature causes the cell to operate at a lower range of current density due to an increase in ohmic and activation overpotentials.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures

Sentencas: Further, increasing the operating pressure and degree of pre-reforming reduces the concentration overpotential and thereby enhances cell performance.
Titulo: Electrochemical study of a planar solid oxide fuel cell: Role of support structures
